Films''' is an Australian film collective and [[production company]],{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/company/co0062793/|title=Blue-Tongue Films [au]|website=IMDb|access-date=2016-07-27}} composed of filmmakers [[Kieran Darcy-Smith]], [[Luke Doolan]], [[Joel Edgerton]], [[Nash Edgerton]], [[Mirrah Foulkes]], Sean Kruck, [[David Michôd]] and [[Spencer Susser]].{{cite web|last=Hawkins|first=Joanne|title=Men of the Year 2010 Winners – Blue-Tongue Films|url=https://www.gq.com.au/men+of+the+year/2010+winners/blue+tongue+films,14551|publisher=gq.com.au|accessdate=18 March 2013|author2=Dawe, James|date=3 December 2010}}{{cite web|last=Cieply|first=Michael|title=Filmmakers With Shared Grit|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/18/movies/18tongue.html|work=nytimes.com|accessdate=18 March 2013|date=17 February 2010}}{{cite web|last=Erbland|first=Kate|title=Joel Edgerton to Star in Twisty Thriller 'Felony' From His Own Script|url=http://www.filmschoolrejects.com/news/joel-edgerton-felony-kerbl.php|publisher=filmschoolrejects.com|accessdate=18 March 2013|date=16 May 2012}} Founded in 1996, Blue-Tongue has created a number of feature films as ''Animal Kingdom'', ''Hesher'', ''The Square'', ''Wish You Were Here'', and ''The Gift'',{{cite web|title=Joel Top 50 2012 Arts – Edgerton and Blue-Tongue Films|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/top50/2012/joel-edgerton/story-fndljfny-1226353136961|publisher=theaustralian.com.au|accessdate=18 March 2013}} several short films, including ''Bear'', ''Crossbow'', ''[[The Magician (2005 film)|The Magician]]'', ''I Love Sarah Jane'', ''Miracle Fish'' and ''Spider'', as well as music videos for artists such as [[Ben Lee]], [[Bob Dylan]], [[Brandon Flowers]], [[Empire of the Sun (band)|Empire of the Sun]], [[Eskimo Joe]], [[Evermore (band)|Evermore]], [[Lana Del Rey]], [[Missy Higgins]], [[Rahzel]], and [[The Veronicas]]. == contentMetadata.text: Blue-Tongue Films is an Australian film collective and production company, composed of filmmakers Kieran Darcy-Smith, Luke Doolan, Joel Edgerton, Nash Edgerton, Mirrah Foulkes, Sean Kruck, David Michôd and Spencer Susser. Founded in 1996, Blue-Tongue has created a number of feature films as Animal Kingdom, Hesher, The Square, Wish You Were Here, and The Gift, several short films, including Bear, Crossbow, The Magician, I Love Sarah Jane, Miracle Fish and Spider, as well as music videos for artists such as Ben Lee, Bob Dylan, Brandon Flowers, Empire of the Sun, Eskimo Joe, Evermore, Lana Del Rey, Missy Higgins, Rahzel, and The Veronicas. "Blue-Tongue Films [au]". IMDb. Retrieved 27 July 2016. Hawkins, Joanne; Dawe, James (3 December 2010). "Men of the Year 2010 Winners – Blue-Tongue Films". gq.com.au. Retrieved 18 March 2013. Cieply, Michael (17 February 2010). "Filmmakers With Shared Grit". nytimes.com. Retrieved 18 March 2013. Erbland, Kate (16 May 2012). "Joel Edgerton to Star in Twisty Thriller 'Felony' From His Own Script". filmschoolrejects.com. Retrieved 18 March 2013. "Joel Top 50 2012 Arts – Edgerton and Blue-Tongue Films". theaustralian.com.au. Retrieved 18 March 2013. Michôd, David (3 June 2010), Animal Kingdom, retrieved 27 July 2016 Saville, Matthew (28 August 2014), Felony, retrieved 27 July 2016 Michôd, David (20 June 2014), The Rover, retrieved 27 July 2016 Edgerton, Nash; Susser, Spencer (1 January 2013), The Captain, retrieved 27 July 2016 Official website Blue-Tongue Films's channel on YouTube
